    "department": "Design",
    "description": "About Juicebox\n\nJuicebox is on a mission to help teams win the talent war.\n\nIn the age of AI, human ingenuity is the ultimate scarce resource. Recruiting is a zero-sum game where you either compete or lose.\n\nTeams at Ramp, Notion, and leading AI labs use Juicebox to power their hiring, alongside 5,000+ customers from early-stage startups to Fortune 500 companies.\n\nWe are on the path to $100M in ARR with 20%+ monthly growth, powering thousands of searches every day and making Juicebox one of the fastest-growing AI SaaS companies in the world.\n\nJuicebox has raised over $116M in funding from lead investors including Sequoia Capital, DST Global, and NFDG. Read more about our $80M Series B https://juicebox.ai/blog/series-b here. Additional investors in Juicebox include Y Combinator, Coatue, Bond, Lux, Verified Capital, and Committed Capital.\n\n\nThe Role: Senior Product Designer\n\nIn the role, you'll tackle questions like:\n\n• How can we delight our users in the first 5 minutes of signing up to Juicebox?\n\n• How can we maximize user visibility for our agentic workflows?\n\nYou will own product features end to end — many of which will be built on LLMs. The role will touch the entire Juicebox platform, including both our core platform and Juicebox agent.\n\nThere is also an opportunity to shape and own the overall Juicebox design language, including collaborating with the design agency working on our landing page, advertising strategy, and more.\n\n\nAbout You\n\n• You've built something from scratch — a startup, project, or feature.\n\n• You've designed user-facing product features (ideally B2B or B2C SaaS).\n\n• You're an expert in Figma\n\n• You enjoy working hard and owning projects.\n\n• You've shown excellence: be it in your education, work experiences, projects, or anything else you can share.\n\n• You take asymmetric bets.\n\n\nNice to have\n\n - You have engineering experience or a CS degree (current tech stack includes: Next.js, React, Node.js)\n\n - You worked on a Product-Led-Growth (PLG) product\n\n - You're interested in the recruitment or talent space\n\n - You’ve dabbled in tools like Cursor and Lovable to take designs from concept to working prototypes",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
